This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it deals with natural language processing and topic modeling. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) because topic modeling is often used in information retrieval systems. Additionally, it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it involves probabilistic models and inference. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it deals with knowledge representation and integration. Finally, it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) because it involves the use of Dirichlet distributions in topic modeling.
